### Database (must complete)

**9. Run Performance Advisor**
```
Dashboard → Advisors → Performance Advisor
Fix: missing FK indexes (causes slow queries on every join).
These are fast to add and high impact.
```

**10. Check database size before launch**
```
Dashboard → Database → Database Health → Database size

Free tier limit: 500 MB
Pro tier: 8 GB (then pay-per-GB)

Warning: when free tier fills up → INSERT and UPDATE operations FAIL SILENTLY.
The error is not obvious: users just stop seeing their data saved.
If approaching 80%: upgrade to Pro before launch.

Monitor size: SELECT pg_size_pretty(pg_database_size(current_database()));
```

**11. Enable Point-in-Time Recovery (for databases > 4GB)**
```
Available on Pro plan and above.
Dashboard → Settings → Add-ons → PITR → Enable
Choose retention window (7 days minimum recommended for production).

Free/Pro daily backup is NOT a substitute for PITR — daily backup means up to 24hrs of data loss.
PITR means up to 1 minute of data loss.
```

---

### Infrastructure (must complete)

**12. Upgrade compute before launch (if expecting > 50 concurrent users)**
```
Free/Nano tier limits:
  60 max DB connections
  0.5 CPU, 256 MB RAM
  No PITR, no read replicas
  Auto-pauses after 7 days inactivity

For production with real users: upgrade to at LEAST Micro (from $10/month)
Dashboard → Settings → Compute and Disk → Upgrade

Quick sizing guide:
  < 100 concurrent users:  Micro ($10/month)
  100-500 concurrent users: Small ($25/month)
  500-2000 concurrent users: Medium ($50/month)
  2000+ concurrent users:   Large+ or add read replicas
```

**13. Free tier auto-pause — prevent or plan for**
```
Free tier: auto-pauses after 7 days of inactivity.
IMPORTANT: restore takes 2-3 minutes.
During restore: ALL requests return 503 errors.
Users who visit your app during restore get a broken experience for up to 3 minutes.

Fix option A (recommended): upgrade to Pro before launch.
Fix option B (free tier only): add a health check that pings your DB every 6 days.
  -- Add as pg_cron job:
  SELECT cron.schedule('keep-alive', '0 0 */6 * *', $$ SELECT 1 $$);
```

---

### Monitoring (complete before launch)

**14. Enable log drains (optional but recommended)**
```
Dashboard → Settings → Log Drains → Add drain
Connect to: Datadog, Grafana, Logflare, or any webhook endpoint.
Sends: Edge Function logs, API gateway logs, auth logs.
```

**15. Subscribe to Supabase status page**
```
status.supabase.com → Subscribe to updates
Or Slack: /feed subscribe https://status.supabase.com/history.atom
Notifies you of outages before your users report them.
```

