## Staging vs Production — Project Strategy

```
NEVER test migrations directly in production.
NEVER use production data in development.

Recommended setup:
  development → local Supabase CLI (supabase start)
  staging      → separate Supabase project (same schema, test data)
  production   → your live Supabase project

Same migrations folder → same schema across all environments.
Different .env files → different project URLs and keys.

Netlify: create separate Netlify sites for staging and production.
Deploy preview URL → staging Supabase project
Production URL → production Supabase project
```

```bash
# .env.local (local dev)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=http://localhost:54321
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=[local anon key]

# .env.staging (committed — no secrets)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://[staging-ref].supabase.co

# Netlify: set SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY separately per environment in dashboard
# Never commit secret keys to any .env file
```

